int32_t DPM_msgRecv ( DPM_MCB *  ptrDPM,
int32_t *  errCode 
)

Description
This is the function which is invoked to receive an IPC message Messages can be received from either:- (a) Local: One thread is trying to control the DPM Profile (b) Remote: One core is trying to control the profile executing on the remote domain. Process all the messages

Parameters
[in]ptrDPMPointer to the DPM module
[out]errCodeError code populated on error
Return values
Success- 0
Error- <0
static int32_t DPM_msgResponseHandler ( DPM_MCB *  ptrDPM,
DPM_Msg *  ptrMessage,
DPM_Msg *  ptrResponseMsg,
int32_t *  errCode 
)
static

Description
This is the registered handler which handles the Response message Response messages are received in lieu of a request. Successful responses will change the profile status and will ensure that the DPM instances across domains are synchronized with each other

Parameters
[in]ptrDPMPointer to the DPM module
[in]ptrMessagePointer to the DPM response message which is to be processed.
[out]ptrResponseMsgNot used
[out]errCodeError code populated on error
Return values
Success- 0
Error- <0
